    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As a fried rice devotee, the trick to making your fried rice not stick is </p>
<p>a) place the rice in the pan a little at a time, and scrape scrape scrape the bottom. Use your spatula like a shovel and keep flipping the rice around. Make little scrubbing motions and the grains moving. It really works. </p>
<p>b) add more oil&#8211;but add it in a little at a time (I use maybe 1/4 teaspoon every time it looks like it needs it) because there&#39;s nothing worse than oily fried rice. </p>
<p>c) use cold rice. I don&#39;t know why, but if I use cold, leftover rice instead of fresh rice, it tends to stick less. </p>
<p>I have excellent kim chi in the fridge. I CANNOT WAIT to try this recipe.</p>
    </div>

